<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="disappointed-adj">disappointed <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ˌdɪsə'pɔɪntɪd/    美 /ˌdɪsə'pɔɪntɪd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>失望的；沮丧的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>One by one, the applicants left the interviewer’s office with disappointed looks on their faces.
一个接着一个，求职者面带失望的表情离开了面试间。</p><footer>2013 山东</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) disappointed at / about / with：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The teacher soon realized why the mother was so disappointed about the grade. 
老师很快就明白了为什么母亲对这个成绩如此失望。</p><footer>2012 上海改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She left the restaurant, disappointed with the bad service. 
对餐馆糟糕的服务非常不满，她离开了。</p><footer>译林⑤ – 3</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) disappointed with / in sb:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m disappointed in you — I really thought I could trust you!
你让我很失望，我原以为可以信任你的！</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) disappointed to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We were <strong>deeply / terribly disappointed</strong> to find the museum was closed.
发现博物馆关闭了，我们非常失望。</p><footer>外研⑧ – 7</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) disappointed + (that) 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My mother said it was a great day, but she was just a little disappointed that it didn’t last a tiny bit longer.
我母亲认为那天很不错，但她还是有点失望，要是持续时间稍微再长点就好了。</p><footer>2009 湖北</footer></div></div>